deeplabcut.pose_estimation_tensorflow.nnet.losses module¶

Source: DeeperCut by Eldar Insafutdinov https://github.com/eldar/pose-tensorflow

deeplabcut.pose_estimation_tensorflow.nnet.losses.huber_loss(labels, predictions, weight=1.0, k=1.0, scope=None)[source]¶
Define a huber loss https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Huber_loss
tensor: tensor to regularize. k: value of k in the huber loss scope: Optional scope for op_scope.

Huber loss: f(x) = if |x| <= k:

0.5 * x^2
else:
k * |x| - 0.5 * k^2
Returns:
the L1 loss op.

http://concise-bio.readthedocs.io/en/latest/_modules/concise/tf_helper.html
